 our most influential authors, illustrators, and translators working in both French and English over the past decades. It belongs on the shelf of every enthusiast of Canadian literature. Bilingual edition.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAuthors, Canadiany20th centuryvBiography. 0aAuthors, Canadiany21st centuryvBiography. 0aCanadian literaturexAwards. 7aREFERENCE / Bibliographies & Indexes.2bisacsh  aAwards.  aCanadian Literature.  aGovernor General’s Literary Awards.  aHistory of Canadian Literature.  aLiterary Prizes.1 aIrvine, Andrew David, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJohnston, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRivère, Edmond, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTolman, Stephanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311127268908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2019z978311127498040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077662804240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780776628042423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780776628042/original  a978-3-11-127268-9  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-127498-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles